And thank you for this little concert. I NEEDED IT!
❤️🙏🏼~Amy

snippet.textDisplay: I so needed this today.  I work in healthcare and this pandemic and the fears surrounding it has really been bringing out my depression due to the physical distancing required, as well as my anxiety when looking at the shortages of PPE in our hospitals across North America.  Today's update from my manager even caused a mild anxiety attack, and hearing these songs were part of what has brought me back down.  Please everyone be praying for those who are working in healthcare, and that the needed PPE will be provided to allow us all to show up to work knowing we will be as safe as we can be.

snippet.textDisplay: In 2018 I was going through a terrible time, my Son was using drugs and we almost lost him. Then I came across Burn the Ships on the radio driving home after work and it gave me hope.  I must have played that song a million times. I would listen every time I felt weak, like that darkness was going to swallow me and everyone around me. I don’t know how God works but I do know this, he used that song to let me know he was with me and my family. Today we are on the other side of that darkness and my family is doing well. It could be coincidence, but I hear it all the time on the radio now and every time it makes me smile because it reminds me that God is with me and my family wherever we go.  I am going to try and come see y’all in St. Augustine in July if this COVID-19 is over, I’m a first responder so until this passes life is kind of upside down.  I would like to say thank you in person for the gift of hope you didn’t know you gave me, and continue to give me through a song. I hope this finds you and your families blessed and well.
